title: Castle crowned as MCAC female athlete of week
text:
Castle crowned as MCAC female athlete of week By: Uncredited Report Error 
Jaycee Castle’s two goals in last week’s 3-2 women’s soccer win earned the Brandon University Bobcats forward Manitoba Colleges Athletic Conference female athlete of the week honours. 
The five-foot-eight Brandonite is second in the conference with eight goals this season. She has helped the Bobcats (5-2-0) clinch a playoff spot and a finish of no worse than second place in the standings. They are three points back of Red River College (6-0-0). 
The Bobcats wrap up their regular season on Oct. 17 when they host the Assiniboine Community College Cougars (1-5-0) in the Prowler Cup.
